{"type":"message","id":"04303a72","parentId":"451eace1","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:00:31.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat poll. Current time is 6:00 PM (Asia/Shanghai) = 10:00 UTC.\n\nI need to read HEARTBEAT.md and follow it strictly. The HEARTBEAT.md rules are:\n\n1. Check Active Task Monitoring\n2. If Status=active and Next has content → spawn or yield\n3. If Status=done → cleanup old done tasks\n\nI also need to check for any alerts per the \"主动提醒\" section.\n\nLet me check the ACTIVE_TASK first to see if the subagent completed. But I should NOT poll. If the subagent finished, the completion event will arrive as a message.\n\n\nThe subagent I spawned earlier was supposed to spawn another subagent for quant strategy enhancement, but I haven't received a completion notification yet. Since it's been about an hour since then, I should check the HEARTBEAT.md file to see if there's any status update or if there are any alerts I need to address.\n\nAccording to the HEARTBEAT.md rules, if the active task is still running, I should just yield and let the scheduler handle it. However, I'm also seeing the \"保持安静\" section which says to stay quiet if it's a non-trading day without anomalies, and since it's a trading day at 6 PM with the market already closed, I should consider that context as well.\n\nLet me check the ACTIVE_TASK.md file to determine whether the task is still active or completed, since that will dictate my next action.","thinkingSignature":"d2c73bf9d5a68d434fa538b64e4c20c51b27d98903833021567cad1f5bdbe4ac"},{"type":"text","text":"先读 HEARTBEAT 和 ACTIVE_TASK，再决定是否需要续跑或保持安静。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vnkazkpczxmi_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vnkazkpczxmi_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provid